‘ Examen subitum ramo frondente pependit.’ We hear in the year 223 B.C. of similar alarms created in the minds of the Romans by a vulture seen in the Forum, and three moons in the sky. On that occasion Flaminius, a plebeian free-thinker‚ had made the gods testify against their interpreters by gaining a complete victory over the Gauls.
